radiographic_examinations.findings: Atelectatic changes at the lung bases; 8 mm hypodensity in segment VIII of the liver likely representing a cyst; hypodensity seen in the duodenal groove, possibly artifactual; right renal hypodensity too small to characterize; mild atherosclerosis of the abdominal aorta; dilated appendix up to 9 mm with minimal wall thickening and surrounding inflammatory changes in the right lower quadrant; a few reactive mesenteric lymph nodes in the pericecal region; heterogeneous appearance of the uterus possibly due to fibroid uterus or adenomyosis; no suspicious bone lesions.
